	<div class="summary">Webb-site is proud to launch the World's first crowd-sourced governance ratings system. Now, with a single click, any logged-in user can anonymously contribute to the average rating of an organisation, including listed companies, governments and others. Also we are launching Webb-site Trust Ratings, where users can rate their trust in company directors, politicians, financial advisers or anyone they can find in Webb-site Who's Who. The system will only be as useful as users make it, so let's get started!</div>

<h2 class="center">Seeking the wisdom of crowds<br>
<span class="headlinedate">1 February 2016</span></h2>
<p>Webb-site is excited to announce the birth of what we believe is the World's first crowdsourced governance ratings system, <strong>Webb-site Governance Ratings</strong>. 
For 17 years, we've been freely expressing our views on the quality of corporate 
and economic governance in Hong Kong and elsewhere. Now, it's your turn. Any 
user who is logged in to his or her Webb-site account can now, with our 
one-click ratings system, anonymously contribute a rating on the governance 
quality of any organisation, including listed companies, on a scale of 0 to 5, 
where 0 is of course the lowest. We will publish the average rating for each 
organisation, but no individual contributions will be identified.</p>
<h3>Let's get started!</h3>
<p>To get started, just <a href="../webbmail/login.asp"><strong>log in</strong></a> with your 
e-mail address and password, then enter the stock code of any HK-listed company 
in the "stock code" box at the top of any page, or search for the organisation 
using the "search organisations" box, also at the top of any page. You can also 
try the special lists of <a href="../dbpub/cat.asp?c=7">HKSAR Advisory Bodies</a> and <a href="../dbpub/cat.asp?c=3">Statutory Bodies</a>, or the list 
of <a href="../dbpub/cat.asp?c=4">Governmental bodies</a>, including the HK 
Executive and Legislative Councils and the Hong Kong SAR and PRC Governments. 
Political parties can be found in our <a href="../dbpub/cat.asp?c=27">politics 
category here</a>.</p>
<p>After you have made some rating contributions, stay logged in and visit the
<a href="../webbmail/myratings.asp">My Ratings</a> page, where all your ratings 
are listed. You can change, update or withdraw your rating on any organisation 
at any time with a single click, it's that simple! To keep the system fresh, any 
ratings older than 1 year will be excluded from the average. You guessed it: 
once we have a decent volume of ratings, we will publish league tables, at least 
for listed companies, showing the best and worst governance ratings and everything 
in between. We also plan to track how they vary over time.</p>
<p>In the meantime, you can see the average rating on the page for each 
organisation. On your <a href="../webbmail/myratings.asp">My Ratings</a> page, you can also drill down to see the 
history of your ratings on an individual entity. User functions can be found in 
the "User" menu at the top of each page.</p>
<p>Webb-site Governance Ratings are intended to be absolute, not relative to a 
particular market or peer group, and have nothing to do with market valuations 
if the organisation is a listed company. Many political parties and non-profit 
organisations are set up as companies incorporated in HK, and Webb-site covers 
all 1.29 million companies registered in HK, so feel free to add your view. You 
don't have to be a shareholder or creditor - you might also be an employee, 
customer or supplier who has formed a view on the governance quality through 
your dealings, or just an interested bystander.</p>
<h3>Trust Ratings</h3>
<p>And why stop there? We're on a roll now. We are also launching <strong>
Webb-site Trust Ratings</strong> for individuals. Do you highly or lowly trust a 
particular company director, politician, statutory body member or just the boss 
of your financial services firm, perhaps? How about your financial adviser? If you can find them in
<a href="../dbpub/searchpeople.asp">Webb-site Who's Who</a>, then you can enter 
a trust rating for them.</p>
<p>Last week, we wrote to over 21,000 active subscribers to our free newsletter, 
introducing a new sign-up and log-in system that allows you to stay logged in 
for up to 1 month. If you have forgotten your password, just
<a href="../webbmail/forgot.asp">click here</a> to receive a reset link, good 
for 12 hours.</p>
<p>If you haven't <a href="../webbmail/join.asp">signed up</a>, why wait? The ratings system will only be as 
useful 
as its users make it through their continuing contributions. Over to you.</p>
